About the Business

The story. Our profile. The 411. You get the idea. Ok, we're gonna keep this quick. Because exceptional quality at lightning fast speed is what we're all about. Blaze Pizza. Head food guy, Executive Chef Bradford Kent (aka "The Pizza Whisperer"). Fresh, made-from-scratch dough. Healthful, artisanal ingredients on the assembly line. Inventive to classic. You decide. Blazing hot oven + dedicated pizzasmith + 180 seconds = fast-fire'd, perfectly crisp perfection. Sound good? Enjoy the rest of your day.…

  • Darci K.

    Elite '2021

    Sacramento, CA
    1180
    744
    7406
    9/11/2017
    3 photos

    Dont walk, Blaze your way to this incredible pizza place.

    Blaze Pizza is AH-MAZING! I have been to several make your own pizza joints, but Blaze stands out far and above any place that Ive been to.

    Whats make your own, you ask? Jump in line, because there is sure to be one. The line moves fast, so take a gander at that big menu above the register. yes, you're seeing correctly. Your own pizza for under $10.00. Thats not even the best part...wait for it...  So, there you are, deciding on what type of pizza you might be craving. You can select from a few of the suggested pizza's, or, create your own. Diner's tip #1- create your own! Select from the variety of sauces. You can mix and match. There is no right or wrong. Just pure yum. Diner's tip #2- try the pesto and have then sauce up the edges of your crust. You wont be anything but happy.
    Then the toppings. Oh the wonderful toppings. Cheeses, veggies, meats..and you can have as much as youd like. Feeling meaty? Just say yes to the italian spicy sausage! Add some pepperoni, a lot of cheese, and your tummy will be beyond happy. Feeling like you want to try something lighter? Have them toss some veggies, and salad stuff on your pizza. As you move down the line, the expert pizza makers behind the counter, are moving and groovin to your pizza tastes. They will gladly help you decide what taste combos are good options.  Diners tip #3 Consider sharing pizza with your friends. It helps when you all choose different toppings. Pizza party in the making!

    Your pizza is all put together, you watch as your creation is carefully put into the pizza oven. Dont despair, by the time you pay, fill your drink cup, and find that perfect seat to enjoy your creation, more than likely, your pizza number will be called, and tummy bliss will soon be yours. The pizza oven takes about 5-8 minutes for your perfect pie to be yours. Be patient, it will seem like eternity, but its not.

    I know that parking in Davis can be tough. Diners tip #4- get there around 11am before the crowds arrive. Parking will be easier, and your tummy will be happy. Want to be hip, and show up around 1 ish for lunch? Wherever you park, its worth a block walk for this location.

    Are you still reading? Excellent! Now go!! Blaze on over for the best pizza around!
